      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/velocity-field-mesh-turbulence"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-hemolysis-index-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index comparison at worst-case operating conditions",
      "description": "Predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) compared against in vitro hemolysis measurements from standardized ASTM F1841 protocol across five operating conditions. RH predictions fall within the experimental scatter band at four of five conditions; the fifth shows a 14% over-prediction consistent with known variability in red blood cell fragility across donor populations. Inherent biological variability in RH measurements was assessed qualitatively by subject-matter experts, with inter-donor coefficient of variation estimated at approximately 18–22% based on literature; however, a formal structured uncertainty quantification linking this aleatory source to the validation metric has not been established."
    }
  ],
