    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels at MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out at Gradation 1 consistent with MRL 2 requirements. CFD predictions of relative hemolysis index satisfy the RH < 1 acceptance criterion across all five worst-case operating conditions. The hemolysis index validation result notes qualitative expert assessment of inter-donor biological variability; this aleatory source is acknowledged in narrative but does not alter the overall credibility determination at MRL 2. The model is accepted as fit for purpose for identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
